Program: Outlook
Title: 08/05/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00r6zms
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 9 May 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Kazakh human rights lawyer Yevgeniy Zhovtis, who was given a four-year jail sentence after accidentally killing a pedestrian in his car - and had a prison opened for him. Also, a former gang member from East London looks ahead to the Olympic games; and the Nairobi office messenger who rides his bicycle for work, fun, and even in competitions - even though he's missing one leg. Show less